<br>
I like Everquest. I wouldn't say that I'm addicted, even though I play it a lot.  I miss it when I don't get to play for a while. So?  I miss ice cream when I don't have it for a while. <br>
<br>
I remember a similar debate over the issue of suicide and Dungeons &amp; Dragons when I was younger...  the problem, just like a lot of others, is that when a person commits suicide, people ask questions - Why? Who was responsible? Who can we blame? This is just another example.   Everyone likes to point fingers.... except at themselves.  <br>
<br>
How many people commit suicide because of problems with gambling, unrequited love, dysfunctional families, or severe depression?  Do you turn around and blame the casinos, the dating sevices, family counsellors, or mental health professionals? Do you blame the family, the parents, or the children?<br>
<br>
I don't like to blame anyone.  I like to hold myself responsible for my situation.   <p><center>
