Anyway: A Sakharra ramble, Acropolis is sort of used to these but this is my first Tholuxe one. I may be right, I may be wrong and I claim to make no sense at all... please feel free to stop reading &gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Here &lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
My ex and I used to refer to the masses of people who just do the 8 hour a day job, go home, eat, watch television and breed, yet make no effort to think as &quot;the sheep&quot;. Anyway the flock looks for something convienient that they dont quite understand and have never experienced to blame all of lifes woes on. In reality though, they live a very dull, unimaginative day to day existance and I think many at least on a subconscious level are bitter about it and wish to condemn all of us to the same existance.<br>
<br>
There are some very common themes... <br>
<br>
Music is a common target, most of the great classical composers were accused of writing the &quot;devil's music&quot; at one time or another much as modern artists are condemed as as bad influences.<br>
<br>
Alternative religions are a nice, easy target for the sheep because if you trash another religion then God is on YOUR side of course. <br>
<br>
Dancing in general is still a target among many religious groups, all that touching and moving MUST be a sin... The combination of dancing and music almost always lead to alchohol and drugs and I dont think I need to go further. <br>
<br>
Throw alchol and drugs together with music and dancing and OMG you have the potential for... Sex. Well sex is a nice target because alot of the major religions say its evil unless used for the purpose of breeding.<br>
<br>
Gaming has been a target for some time as well, gambling, pinball, AD&amp;D and for the last 10 years or so video games.<br>
<br>
Anyway, the sheep feel a need to attack anything that &quot;we&quot; use to escape the mundane day to day boredom that they seem to relish. We're not allowed to have any fun and lord forbid we enjoy our lives when they can not. These are the people who sit happily on their couches tuned in to the television from 6:00PM to 11:00PM every night. The sheep are the ones who buy the products that keep the advertising money flowing in to the television stations.<br>
<br>
Ok Sakharra is going to go WAY off the deep end here, if you have read this far, you probabily want to stop because I'm going to make no sense at all while spouting out a sort of paranoid theory.<br>
<br>
So here we are, nearly half of a million people spanning from early baby boomers to post generation X young teens and we're spending 5 or more hours a night or so playing a game and not watching television. Our numbers grow daily as do the number of games we can play. If we're not watching television, we're not being force fed the advertising that drives the income of the networks. <br>
<br>
So is it any surprise that the network news would attack Everquest ?<br>
<br>
The really sad thing is, they view us as isolated in front of our computers yet never realize that we are FAR less isolated than they are sitting glued to their television sets. We meet and experience a multitude of people in our world, we have real conversations, we agree, disagree, make friends and enemies all with real people who just happen to be sitting on the next block or on the other half of the world. All they have are two dimensional talking heads acting out scripts written by people paid to capture their attention. I feel just a bit sorry for them. <br>
<br>
