<br>
As a child, when you are frightened that the monster who lives in your closet is going to burst out of there and eat you while you're sleeping, you latch onto your teddy, pull the covers up over your head and close your eyes because if you can't see it, it sure can't see you!  When that doesn't work you scream for your parents.  Lights come on, fill the room, you're encircled by loving arms and feel safe, loved.<br>
<br>
As you get older, you follow the cattle because you feel wanted, accepted and loved.  You laugh, you smile, you have a good time.  Must follow the cattle, the cattle love you.<br>
<br>
You go to a boring school, listening to boring teachers, conforming yourself to what is accepted by society.  You look at the kids who show their individuality and stick your nose in the air, tease them, pick at them, fight with them.  Gotta love the Mickey Mouse High School Drama Trauma Soaps.<br>
<br>
Your parents expect one thing, religion expects one thing, society expects one thing, your friends expect one thing and the only way to be accepted is to try to please them all.<br>
<br>
Oh... whats this... Everquest?  Oh cool, that looks neat, think I'll buy it.<br>
<br>
WOW... now here is a place that I can be true to myself...<br>
<br>
You quit going to church, you only went because it was expected of you.  You quit your job, not going anywhere in it, dead end, you can't stand it.  Your significant other leaves you because you are no longer conforming yourself to his/her standards.  You are start to be true to yourself and for a while, you are happy.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> *knock knock*</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Who is it?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Life.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
You suck, go away.  I'm busy.<br>
