As for an earlier post about escapism...yes...I'll admit it I'm the first one to find escape in real life.  I get shat on in real life so much that my friends tend to think of me as &quot;unlucky&quot; in all things pertaining to life...and so I like doing other things I have so many hobbies it isn't funny.  But when it comes down to it my friends have always been there to support me and pull me away from the game to go work out or party or whatever...and honestly...not always do even these things compare to the pure fun I have when playing EQ...I'm proud of my dorf and I'm happy to know the people in my guild and others in the game.  &quot;Its just a game&quot; I don't think is true and VI is full of shit but they always are so no diff there.  It IS more than a game...Will you commit suicide over it? Hell no! Will things in game affect you IRL?  YES.  Will they cause you to be depressed?  I sure hope not.  IF they do then find a new game to play...anyone doing something for entertainment...even escaping should take responsibility for playing something that affects them negatively.<br>
<br>
My advice: EQ is an amazing game.  Is it truly addictive? NO.  I played it more when I first started when the game first came out and played it for many months hours on end.  Then I decided that I'd stop and spend more time with my, at the time, girlfriend and eventually I didn't miss it.  I came back 3 years later because I remembered how great this game really is.  If I decided to stop playing now I'd miss it but I wouldn't say no to change.  If you are that addicted then maybe they have a point about it being like &quot;crack&quot;.  I kinda think of it more like &quot;Everweed&quot; in that weed is good shit and you wanna have it when you can.  You'll spend a monthly budget on it, but the fact is that you are never truly addicted to the stuff and if you wanted to you can stop smoking it forever after. <p>Rundo Nundodundo
